Army psychiatrist Major Nidal Hasan opened fire on Fort Hood, Texas, on November 5, 2009, killing 13 men and women .
Authorities initially classed the mass murder as ‘workplace violence’ but it has since been acknowledged that the attack was an act of terrorism .
One victim claims he is still going without certain benefits after the military rejected his claims that his injuries were sustained in the line of duty .
Army spokeswoman said the Army has determined that victims will receive benefits 'to which they are legally entitled'